<br>
It's an insult to the cook to overdo the condiments, especially before you taste the food. I've taken supper away from the kids for doing that.<br>
<br>
2.  Salt added on meat during the cooking phase toughens the meat.<br>
<br>
3. My old idea of a perfectly cooked steak was march the cow around a fire three times, slaughter it and serve. Now adays I tend towards medium rare.<br>
