<br>
A1 on the baked potato ain't bad for a bit of a change.<br>
<br>
Most people that eat their steaks anything past medium are either uncultured or hypochondriacs.  I personally enjoy a good carpacchio (raw beef) so rare to med-rare suits me fine.  You must remember that the cut of beef also determines which temperature u should ask for.  A good Filet will be a 2-3&quot; tall medallion.  I typically ask for these to be cooked Medium-Rare as often times asking for a steak of this thickness to be rare achieves you a nice cold center (yuk).  On the other hand, a Strip or Porterhouse is not as thick so i ask for these to be rare. <br>
